Should we be checking for (and selectively not registering) patterns which have a high likelihood of messing with other autoconverts already registered in the editor?

For example:
{code}
  "matchers": [
    { "pattern": "http://{}" }
    { "pattern": "https://{}" }
    { "pattern": "{}" }
  ]
{code}

It would be fairly straightforward to implement this in the autoconvert javascript, although this has the downside of failing silently from the perspective of the add-on developer.

For each pattern, allow the definition of default values for the mapped macro.

{code}
"autoconvert": {
  "urlParameter": "url",
  "matchers": [
    { "pattern": "http://docs.google.com/d/document{}/edit" }
    { "pattern": "http://docs.google.com/d/spreadsheet{}/edit" }
    { "pattern": "http://docs.google.com/d/presentation{}/edit" }
  ]
}
{code}

Extend the "matchers" object to include parameter values.

{code}
  {
    "pattern": "http://docs.google.com/d/document{}/edit",
    "parameters": {
      "width": "100px",
      "height": "100px"
    }
  }
{code}

This will set the parameter values for "width" and "height" both to 100px if this pattern is matched.

h2. Context
Our Comala Approvals addon allows you to Approve/Reject a page, from a Content Byline Connect Module. You click in the byline and approve and reject. The Status (Aproved/Rejected) is show in the content byline.

h2. Scenario 1
 When you Approve/Reject we want to change the byline to display the new status automagically, without having to reload the page.

We are achieving that right now, by using {{getContentProperty}} and {{setContentProperty}}. Which is silly because we are making extra Rest calls (remember the kittens) :(

What we would like to have is a simple way to update the byline. It would be great to have something like
{code}
AP.require('confluence', function(confluence){
  confluence.updateByline({key: propertyKey});
});
{code}
Just that!

h2. Scenario 2 
This is more complex. Once a page is _approved_ and the page is update, we listen to page updates and change the status (i.e. to _for review_). 

Problem is that when the page is re-rendered, and the by-lined read, we have not processed the webhook and change the status... 

So.. to deal with this one, we have a web-panel with a script which would look up the page metadata, if it has been update recently, then we would reset the page status, yet again. Plus it could cause a race condition... 

So, if we had something like the {{updateByline}} we would just get it updated.

